# VISUALIZATION OF THE VARIABLES
In [15]:
df_brokerage = df.groupby('broker_name').agg({'firm_x_sales':['count','sum','mean'],
                               'total_industry_sales':['count','sum','mean']})
df_citystate = df.groupby('city_state').agg({'firm_x_sales':['count','sum','mean'],
                               'total_industry_sales':['count','sum','mean']})
df_territory = df.groupby('territory').agg({'firm_x_sales':['count','sum','mean'],
                               'total_industry_sales':['count','sum','mean']})
df_fundcategory = df.groupby('fund_category').agg({'firm_x_sales':['count','sum','mean'],
                               'total_industry_sales':['count','sum','mean']})
df_email = df.groupby('email_open').agg({'firm_x_sales':['count','sum','mean'],
                               'total_industry_sales':['count','sum','mean']})
df_web = df.groupby('web_visit').agg({'firm_x_sales':['count','sum','mean'],
                               'total_industry_sales':['count','sum','mean']})
df_webcast = df.groupby('webcast_attendee').agg({'firm_x_sales':['count','sum','mean'],
                               'total_industry_sales':['count','sum','mean']})
df_marketing = df.groupby('marketing_engaged').agg({'firm_x_sales':['count','sum','mean'],
                               'total_industry_sales':['count','sum','mean']})
df_brokerage_top = df_brokerage[df_brokerage['firm_x_sales']['count'] > 10000]
df_citystate_top = df_citystate[df_citystate['firm_x_sales']['count'] > 5000]
df_territory_top = df_territory[df_territory['firm_x_sales']['count'] > 10000]
df_fundcategory_top = df_fundcategory[df_fundcategory['firm_x_sales']['count'] > 25000]

# Firm X Sales
# Brokerage Chart

fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=3, ncols=1,sharex=True,figsize=(12, 12))
axes[0].ticklabel_format(useOffset=False,style='plain')
df_brokerage_top['firm_x_sales']['sum'].plot(ax=axes[0], kind='bar',title="Sum of Sales")
df_brokerage_top['firm_x_sales']['mean'].plot(ax=axes[1], kind='bar',title="Mean of Sales")
df_brokerage_top['firm_x_sales']['count'].plot(ax=axes[2], kind='bar',title="Count of Sales")
plt.xticks(rotation = 90)
plt.xlabel("Brokers")
plt.setp(axes[0], ylabel='Sum')
plt.setp(axes[1], ylabel='Mean')
plt.setp(axes[2], ylabel='Count')
plt.suptitle("Firm X Sales on Top Brokerage",size = 25)
plt.show()
